HEADWORD: bortsch
<hw>bortsch</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russian]</ety> <def>a Russian soup
usually containing beet juice as a foundation, and often served with
sour cream. Also, as used in the U.S., a sour cabbage soup, called in
Russian <altname>shchi</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> borsch, borsh, borscht, borshch, bortsch.</syn>⟦br⟧
